	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I made a post on this guy earlier.  I was lvl 52 and I was at half mana when I started.  My 2nd mistake was actualy trying to nuke him.  My 3rd mistake was I started fighting him on top of the hill, instead of pulling him to a safer spot.<BR>
<BR>
Now I'm lvl 56, and I can own this puppy.  Upon reflection, I think a lvl 49 mage could solo him too.  You just might have to chain cast like 10 pets.<BR>
<BR>
The strategy now is simple, albeit, still dangerous.  Dont try this if you have any lag...<BR>
<BR>
Pull him with debuff (malosi), then just let pet tank.  When pet is about 20% HP, start casting new one and get the /pet get lost   command ready.  I have Jboots, so if I mess up and he kills pet before I'm done casting the new one, your ONLY choice is to run for zone or gate (thanks verant for not giving mages snare/fear/root/mez/mem blur etc.<BR>
<BR>
The only nukes I even consider using on him are my AoE rain nukes.  Because those are extremly mana efficient.  But pets still remain the most mana efficient damage I have.  My lvl 49 fire pets cost 200 mana, and will deal out about 2-4k damage usually.  Against a mob that hit's like this sucker does, the pet will deal only like 800-1k damage, but that still is a deal for 200 mana.  <BR>
<BR>
My lvl 55 AoE spell is 3 waves of 630 for 400 mana.  So almost 2k damage for 400 mana is good, but he must have Malosi stuck first and he must not move while the rain is going.  So he must already be very aggroed on pet.<BR>
<BR>
This fight is not really worth it, because normal HG seem to drop the same loot, and ONE unbuffed lvl 49 fire pet can solo a HG, then I can reclaim it so I only spent like 70 mana.  I mainly like to kill this guy now for revenge.<BR>
<BR>
So importantly, dont waste your mana nuking if you are a mage, just chain cast pets.  If you have a group that wants to fight him SLOW HIM!!  Slow would make this guy very managible. To confirm the other notes about him...<BR>
<BR>
he's lvl 46<BR>
he double hits for 121<BR>
he has about 8-9k HP<BR>
he has high resists<BR>
he drops normal HG loot.<BR>
<BR>
Good hunting to you all!<BR>
<BR>
Eandori Raintree<BR>
High elf Conjuror of the 56th circle
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
