	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				My group took this guy out last night.  Our Cleric, Bendok, pulled the mob not realizing how tough he was and the battle was on.  We had a 45th Cleric, 40th Druid (Luvdare), 41st Paladin (Fewlio), 35th Ranger (Styleth) and myself, 36th Paladin (Kneesmasher).  <BR>
<BR>
We began the battle and soon realized that our melee hits were having little or no affect. In the time a regular HG would have fallen, he was only down about a 1/4th of his points.  We reevaluated and considered backing out of the fray, but decided we could take this guy out. Everyone gritted their teeth for the gruelling battle.  Bendok came in with some GREAT heals, Fewlio tanked the Big Guy while Styleth and I added what damage we could.  I taunted when I needed to get his attention but with his hits in the 120's and I couldn't take it for long. <BR>
<BR>
Our wonderful Druid, Luvdare, stepped up and got his attention and began to kite him slowly around while he was snared.  We continued to add damage along the way.  Bendok medded when he could and when he had too, and the fierce battle continued for many long minutes. <BR>
<BR>
Finally with some mighty blows and some well timed nukes, he fell. No great loot...just regular HG-type loot. Kinda disappointing but a GREAT and challenging battle for all of us!<BR>
<BR>
I'd like to take him on again!! But not by myself....hehe<BR>
<BR>
Kneesmasher Ayebulger<BR>
36th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<BR>
Twilight Brethren<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;
